· Engineered Chroococcidiopsis producing ≥0.5 g O₂/m²/day in Mars simulation chamber at 50 mbar, 0°C, surviving 500 Gy cumulative dose.
· Perchlorate reduction: ≥90% ClO₄⁻ reduction in MGS-1 simulant within 30 Earth days at 0°C.
· Biocontainment: Zero escape events in 12-month test campaign; ncAA-free kill confirmed within 5 doublings; all six containment layers functional.
· Consortium stability: Three-strain consortium maintained for ≥90 days in Mars-simulated bioreactor.
· Full DBTL cycle completed autonomously (no human intervention) at simulated 48-minute latency, achieving ≥5 complete cycles.
· AI latency adaptation: Bayesian optimization successfully tuned for delayed feedback environment.

