2. Long-term monitoring of organism population evolution under direct Martian radiation and diurnal cycling.
3. Continuous AI-driven optimization — organisms at this stage have undergone hundreds of DBTL cycles and are the product of AI-guided directed evolution under actual Martian selection conditions.

Note on terraforming timescale: Even under optimistic projections, biological contribution to atmospheric-scale oxygen increase (from 0.13% to breathable levels) would require centuries to millennia at the scales addressable by early MABES deployments. Phase 3 of MABES is not terraforming. It is the empirical demonstration that self-sustaining biological oxygen production is achievable on a planetary surface other than Earth. That demonstration is the primary scientific contribution.

